A man has been cleared of attacking two pensioners on a cruise ship after claiming he acted in self-defence.Graeme Finlay, 53, from Glasgow, had become involved in an altercation with Ron Phillips, 70, and his 68-year-old wife June as the ship cruised around Lanzarote in January last year.The incident stemmed from Mr Finlay feeling they snubbed him at dinner when he was sat at their table.